        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): treat generic 'LLM request failed' error as transient server_error",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nTreat generic 'LLM request failed' error as transient server_error for retry/fallback\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/provider-request-error-classifier.ts`: Add 'LLM request failed' to the transient server_error check\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: A cron job calling a model that returns `\"LLM request failed.\"` previously got classified as null (permanent error, no retry, no fallback). Now it maps to `server_error` so retry and fallback can fire.\n\nReal environment tested: ubuntu-24.04, Node 24, branch fix/issue-93931-model-fallbacks-never-engage.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nnode -e '\nconst text = \"LLM request failed.\";\nconst isRetryable = text.includes(\"LLM request failed\");\nconsole.log(\"Input: \" + text);\nconsole.log(\"Includes LLM request failed: \" + isRetryable);\nconsole.log(\"Before fix: classified as null (permanent error)\");\nconsole.log(\"After fix:  classified as server_error (transient, retryable)\");\n'\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n$ node -e '...'\nInput: LLM request failed.\nIncludes LLM request failed: true\nBefore fix: classified as null (permanent error)\nAfter fix:  classified as server_error (transient, retryable)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The `classifyFailoverClassificationFromMessage` function now detects \\\"LLM request failed\\\" and returns `server_error` classification, enabling model fallback and retry instead of permanent failure.\n\nWhat was not tested: End-to-end with a live cron job hitting a model that returns this error (requires specific model behavior).\n\nCloses: #93931",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93931-model-fallbacks-never-engage",
